The Rat Patrol - Season 2 - Complete

During World War II in 1942, the North African campaign was one of the hot spots. The Germans had a strong presence. The thorn in the Germans' side came in the form of four men in two Jeeps -- THE RAT PATROL.

The Rat Patrol
American television series
Four Allied soldiers roam the North African desert in machine-gun-equipped Jeeps during World War II, harrying Rommel's Afrika Korps. Their frequent foe is honorable German officer Dietrich. Occasionally, the enemies join forces against a common foe.
Final episode date: March 18, 1968
Theme song: The Rat Patrol Theme Song
Network: American Broadcasting Company
